Named externs (compiler-rt libcalls) on plan9: each name gets a phantom atom
with a GOT slot, resolved at flush against the same-named zcu export
(fail-by-name if missing). CodeGen's genExternSymbolRef and the Select
.symbol operand emit ds-relative GOT loads/calls; Lower promotes call/jmp
memory operands to 64-bit (call m32 has no encoding). Robustness: bases
initialized in createEmpty (the in-process cmdBuild flow never calls open(),
which was the only place setting them — atoms all landed at offset ~0 and
the header entry was 0); entry derived from the _start export's atom offset
after layout (writeSyms's name scan read a garbage sym value on this path);
flushModule validates/reopens a dead emit fd and reports kernel errstr on
write failures; seeNav allocates got_index on the found-existing path;
getOffset handles .memory/.indirect operands.

